snippet.textDisplay:
These people have been left undisturbed and their Thousands of years of culture,  heritage, ancient   religion and amassed lands have stayed private. The government has provided the facilities in terms of gas, electric and Internet services. It takes approximately four hours to get to their location from my family home, as my relatives live in northern Pakistan as well.  They visited our valleys and we have visited theirs. 

The haters out there you know very little about the world including Pakistan will see from the people of Chitral and many other tribes you’ve never seen or heard about - these people are never converted or their lands stolen. We’ve all be left alone in our scenic and unspoilt beautiful valleys. 

My grandparents have told me that the government has always helped them, particularly to get electric into valley in order to elevate difficulties.
